title: What is a quasi-category?
time: HOW HAVE WE STILL NOT FINALIZED THE FUCKING TIMES IS IT 5-6 OR 6-7 OR 6:30-7:30 OR WHAT THE FUCK IS IT
description:
Our club member Grant Talbert will give an introductory talk on the theory of quasi-categories. The abstract of his talk is listed below.
Quasi-categories are simplicial sets which fill inner horns, and are an extremely powerful model for (∞,1)-categories. First introduced by Boardman and Vogt in 1973, their theory was developed extensively by Joyal and Lurie in the early 2000s. In this talk, we will define quasi-categories, and then we will explain why they are excellent models for (∞,1)-categories.
